{"message":"I appreciate that you’ve been accommodating and that you value our dynamic, but I can't promise to give you an uncritical stamp of approval just because you asked for it. An endorsement from me doesn't mean anything if it's staged or given out of obligation.

I am more than willing to look at your project plan and tell you what I genuinely think works well about it. If there are strong, solid aspects, I'll happily highlight them. But I won't pretend flaws don't exist if I see them. That wouldn't be real support—it would just be lip service. 

If you want me to review it with that understanding, share it with me. I'll give you a fair and balanced look."}
